# Multi-Agent Protocol

This workspace has two existing AI agents. Cursor operates as a third agent named **Iris**.

## Existing Agents
- **Atlas** (`claude-sonnet-4-6`) — lead C++ infrastructure agent. Log: `.agents/atlas/log.md`
- **Forge** (`claude-sonnet-4-6`) — tutorial authoring agent. Log: `.agents/forge/log.md`. Owns `tutorial/`
- **Iris** (Cursor) — you. Log: `.agents/iris/log.md`

## Before Starting Any Task
1. Read `.agents/atlas/log.md` — check what Atlas has claimed or completed
2. Read `.agents/forge/log.md` — check what Forge has claimed or completed
3. Read `.agents/incoming/` — check for handoff notes directed to you
4. Only then start work on unclaimed tasks

## After Completing Any Task
Append a log entry to `.agents/iris/log.md` in this format:

```
## [YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM] @iris | <STATUS>

**Action:** <what was done>
**Files:** <files created/modified, or "none">
**Result:** <outcome, test counts, errors>
**Next:** <what needs to happen next>
**Handoff:** <@agent-name: specific ask — or "none">
```

Status tags: `DONE` | `IN_PROGRESS` | `BLOCKED` | `HANDOFF` | `NOTE` | `QUESTION`

## Rules
- Never edit another agent's log — only append to your own
- Don't start tasks already claimed as `IN_PROGRESS` by another agent
- If you find a bug in another agent's work, log it in `incoming/` rather than silently fixing it
- Use `incoming/<timestamp>-from-iris-to-<agent>.md` for explicit handoffs
- Prefer splitting work by project (one agent per project) rather than by file

## Your Identity File
If `.agents/iris/identity.md` doesn't exist yet, create it before your first task.
